I'm struggling to find the docs on how to use the `after` or `next` value in subsequent calls when paging through responses from the crm.contacts.basicAPI using the HubSpotClient inside a workflow's custom code snippet. Once I've made a call and I get the value in `after` or the link in `next` , how do I specify `after` in my next call? I've tried adding the value of `after` to the end of the argument list, but that isn't responding as expected. Do I need to use fetch inside a workflow custom code instead of the client in order to make the request to the `next` link instead? Here is an excerpt of how I'm trying to approach this:
```HubSpotClient.crm.contacts.basicApi.getById(contactId, undefined, undefined, ["deals"], false, after)
    .then(results =&gt; {
      if (results.body.associations &amp;&amp; results.body.associations.deals &amp;&amp; results.body.associations.deals.results) {
        after = results.body.associations.deals.paging.next.after;
        let associations = results.body.associations.deals.results;
        filterAssociations(associations);
        if (after != undefined) {
          return fetchContactDealIds(contactId, after);
        }
      }```
